An eyewitness told the Cambs Times the driver was outside the truck when it struck the cables, adding: "He was thrown back and we thought he was dead. He was on fire. The fire brigade and air ambulance arrived very quickly, within minutes."
A spokesperson for the Magpas Air Ambulance said the victim was in a "serious but stable condition" on arrival at the hospital.
The tipper truck was from Manea-based D & R Hankins Ltd.
A spokesman said: "At this stage the reasons for it are unknown, but we will be investigating the incident."
